---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import PackageLadder from '../../components/sections/PackageLadder.astro';
import { sitePath } from '../../lib/paths';
import { copywritingAddOns } from '../../data/offer-site';
---
<MarketingLayout title="Pricing | FrontDoor Web Co." description="Professional local business website packages starting at $3,500.">
  <section class="content-section"><div class="container prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
    <h1>Website pricing and launch paths</h1>
    <p>Choose the level of website strategy, copy support, layout work, and ongoing care that fits the business. Final scope is confirmed after intake so the project starts with clear expectations.</p>
  </div></section>

  <PackageLadder heading="Choose the right launch path" intro="Starter, Professional, Custom Layout, and Monthly Care are separate offers with different levels of strategy, design translation, and ongoing support." />

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Project terms</p>
      <h2>Typical timeline and payment structure</h2>
      <p>Most standard launches take 7-14 business days after assets, copy direction, and approvals are received. Custom layouts, missing assets, delayed feedback, or deeper copywriting can extend the schedule.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container pricing-grid">
      <article class="premium-card">
        <h3>Payment</h3>
        <p>Typical projects use a deposit to reserve the build and a final payment before launch. Larger custom projects may use milestone billing.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="premium-card">
        <h3>Revision scope</h3>
        <p>One focused revision round is included with launch packages. New pages, new direction, rewritten strategy, or added features are scoped separately.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="premium-card">
        <h3>Client inputs</h3>
        <p>Launch timing depends on receiving accurate business details, photos or proof if available, copy feedback, approvals, and fact-checking.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container comparison-section" aria-labelledby="not-included">
      <p class="eyebrow">Scope boundaries</p>
      <h2 id="not-included">What is not included unless specifically quoted</h2>
      <div class="comparison-grid">
        <article class="comparison-card">
          <h3>Marketing and creative extras</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Logo design or full brand identity</li>
            <li>Professional photography or video</li>
            <li>Google Ads or social media campaigns</li>
            <li>Advanced SEO or ranking guarantees</li>
            <li>Ongoing content writing beyond selected scope</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="comparison-card">
          <h3>Software and platform features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>E-commerce or payment systems</li>
            <li>Booking systems, CRM, dashboards, or logins</li>
            <li>Custom backend, database, or automation</li>
            <li>Extra revision rounds</li>
            <li>New pages after the approved scope</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container two-col">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Custom layout</p>
        <h2>Have a sketch or custom layout?</h2>
        <p>Sketches, mood boards, and custom page structures are welcome, but they move the project into the Custom Layout Build tier. That work requires custom homepage wireframing, section planning, a design mockup pass, responsive QA, extra review time, and may affect timeline.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="premium-card">
        <h3>What changes in scope</h3>
        <p>Custom layout projects translate rough direction into buildable page sections instead of using the standard launch system. That is why they start at a higher tier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Copywriting add-on</p>
      <h2>What if the website copy is not ready?</h2>
      <p>If you already have usable copy, we polish and place it. If you have rough notes, we can turn those notes into website-ready pages. If there is no usable copy yet, deeper copywriting and positioning can be added to the project.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container pricing-grid">
      {copywritingAddOns.map((item) => (
        <article class="price-card">
          <span>Copy support</span>
          <h3>{item.name}</h3>
          <strong>{item.price}</strong>
          <p>{item.description}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
    <div class="container copy-note">
      <p>Final copywriting scope depends on how much accurate raw material you provide. We do not invent credentials, guarantees, licenses, years in business, or claims you have not confirmed. Client review and fact-checking are required before launch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>How pricing is finalized</h2>
      <p>Final pricing is confirmed after intake based on page count, copy depth, asset readiness, special layout needs, and revision scope. You will know the project range before work begins.</p>
      <p><a class="button-primary" href={sitePath('offer-site/contact')}>Request a Launch Plan</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
